As illustrated in Figure 1, the evaluation of RF(
Δ α
) requires two primary inputs: WTOA, namely the incoming solar irradiance at the top of the atmosphere, derived from astronomical relationships; and Win, namely the incident solar irradiance at ground level, measured continuously by means of albedometers.

To improve the robustness of the estimate, the RF(
Δ α
) values obtained from Eq. (1) are calibrated using discrete Sentinel-2 satellite observations. For each overpass i, a calibration factor ki is introduced and defined as the ratio between the satellite-derived albedo and the simultaneously measured ground albedo. The calibrated expression therefore becomes (Eq. (2)):

